cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ai-audit-trail in academic, regulatory, or audit-evidence contexts, please cite it as below."
title: "ai-audit-trail: Cryptographically verifiable audit trails for AI systems"
abstract: >-
  ai-audit-trail is a Python library producing tamper-evident, Ed25519-signed
  and SHA-256 hash-chained Decision Receipts for every decision made by an AI
  system. It includes built-in compliance mappings to ISO 42001, the NIST AI
  Risk Management Framework, and EU AI Act articles 9, 12, 13, 17, and 18, as
  well as drop-in adapters for FastAPI, LangChain, the OpenAI SDK, and the
  Anthropic SDK. Receipts can be exported as offline-verifiable evidence
  packages and validated by external auditors without runtime system access.
type: software
